WEBVTT

01:36.080 --> 01:37.720
ADAPTED FROM THE NOVEL OF THE SAME NAME
BY ZHU YI ON WWW.JJWXC.NET

01:37.800 --> 01:42.280
NANWU UNIVERSITY, ORIENTATION DAY

01:42.360 --> 01:45.240
SLEEP EARLY, RISE EARLY
SAY NO TO STAYING UP LATE

01:45.320 --> 01:46.280
Hello, my friend.

01:49.320 --> 01:50.280
We've got a new roommate.

01:50.360 --> 01:51.720
A big welcome

01:51.800 --> 01:53.200
To our new roommate

01:53.280 --> 01:54.720
A big welcome

01:54.800 --> 01:55.880
To…

01:58.360 --> 02:00.160
All right. Now that we're all here,

02:00.240 --> 02:01.280
let me say a few words.

02:01.360 --> 02:03.120
We've been assigned

02:03.200 --> 02:04.520
to the same dorm for four years at uni.

02:04.600 --> 02:06.480
That's got to be fate.

02:06.560 --> 02:07.520
Don't you think?

02:07.600 --> 02:08.520
Fate brought me to you?

02:08.600 --> 02:10.320
Well, there goes my college experience.

02:10.400 --> 02:11.680
Chen Junwen,

02:11.760 --> 02:13.280
listen. I've put up
with you for long enough.

02:13.360 --> 02:15.000
If we weren't high school classmates,

02:15.080 --> 02:18.040
I'd have switched dorms
and roommates already.

02:18.120 --> 02:18.960
Sure, go for it.

02:19.040 --> 02:20.480
- I'm not switching anymore.
- Do it right now.

02:20.560 --> 02:21.480
I'll stay here to annoy you every day.

02:21.560 --> 02:22.840
- I'll drive you crazy.
- Excuse me.

02:22.920 --> 02:23.880
- Excuse me.
- I'll drive you…

02:27.320 --> 02:30.160
This chubby guy here is Qian Fei,
and I'm Chen Junwen.

02:30.240 --> 02:31.600
We're both majoring in AI.

02:31.680 --> 02:33.160
- Hey, man.
- What about you two?

02:33.800 --> 02:35.200
I'm Duan Jiaxu,
majoring in Computer Science.

02:35.280 --> 02:37.000
- Hello.
- You look good.

02:39.160 --> 02:41.200
He's my classmate. Not the chatty type.

02:41.280 --> 02:43.040
- His name is…
- Sang Yan.

02:43.120 --> 02:44.360
Such a deep voice.

02:44.440 --> 02:47.640
Sang Yan!

02:49.280 --> 02:50.600
Man, I missed you!

02:50.680 --> 02:52.800
Why aren't we in the same dorm?

02:52.880 --> 02:54.520
I was really hoping to be your roommate.

02:54.600 --> 02:55.560
I'm in the building next door.

02:58.320 --> 02:59.240
That's quite the greeting.

03:01.400 --> 03:03.560
Hey, who here is having trouble
dealing with him?

03:04.720 --> 03:07.080
Awesome! Let's swap rooms.

03:09.320 --> 03:10.920
Dude, we'd much rather

03:11.000 --> 03:13.400
share a room with a quiet cool guy

03:13.480 --> 03:15.720
than a walking loudspeaker.

03:15.800 --> 03:16.920
You don't know me well enough.

03:17.000 --> 03:18.760
Anyone who does
will tell you I'm the cool type.

03:18.840 --> 03:20.080
- Oh? You're a cool guy, too?
- And I'm very quiet.

03:20.160 --> 03:21.280
What bothers you most when you sleep?

03:21.360 --> 03:22.560
Snoring is the worst for me.

03:22.640 --> 03:26.000
I hate it when people
grind their teeth at night.

03:26.080 --> 03:27.800
- You know, he…
- Knock it off.

03:27.880 --> 03:28.920
When did I ever grind my teeth?

03:29.000 --> 03:30.400
Even my parents never said that.

03:30.480 --> 03:32.320
Sang Yan, what bothers you the most?

03:32.400 --> 03:33.840
Noise.

03:40.320 --> 03:41.720
Snoring and teeth grinding are nothing.

03:41.800 --> 03:43.440
Yeah. The worst

03:43.520 --> 03:44.840
is when someone sleepwalks at night.

03:44.920 --> 03:47.120
Waking up to that is terrifying.

03:58.680 --> 03:59.800
3,248 DAYS

03:59.880 --> 04:05.080
DAY 186 OF LIVING TOGETHER OFFICIALLY

04:52.320 --> 04:54.960
I must have sleepwalked
into the wrong room

04:55.040 --> 04:56.200
and ended up in the wrong bed.

04:58.000 --> 04:59.560
That's the only explanation.

05:49.640 --> 05:50.560
Wen Yifan.

05:52.320 --> 05:53.360
Why are you here?

05:56.120 --> 05:57.520
Explain yourself.

06:04.200 --> 06:05.040
You're dreaming.

06:08.520 --> 06:11.000
Once you wake up,
things will be back to normal.

06:22.960 --> 06:24.560
Do I look that dumb to you?

06:29.520 --> 06:31.040
Just keep sleeping.

06:31.120 --> 06:32.200
You'll look normal once you wake up.

07:10.400 --> 07:11.360
Leaving in a hurry, huh?

07:19.640 --> 07:20.480
What was that?

07:25.400 --> 07:26.240
Look,

07:28.320 --> 07:32.080
I'm not trying to ignore
what happened this morning,

07:32.160 --> 07:33.360
but I really have to go.

07:33.440 --> 07:35.880
I have an interview scheduled,
and I'm kind of running late.

07:35.960 --> 07:37.960
Can we talk when I get back tonight?

07:41.040 --> 07:42.200
No, we can't.

07:44.520 --> 07:45.480
Tell me now.

07:46.320 --> 07:47.160
What was going on earlier?

07:47.240 --> 07:48.600
I was sleepwalking.

07:49.840 --> 07:52.640
It's not exactly something I can control.

07:52.720 --> 07:55.520
Didn't you say before
that you wouldn't come into my room?

07:55.600 --> 07:57.840
I honestly have no idea
what happened this time.

07:59.280 --> 08:02.440
It's totally on me,
but I promise it won't happen again.

08:03.640 --> 08:04.720
Honestly,

08:06.720 --> 08:08.280
I'm a little scared.

08:08.960 --> 08:10.760
I have no idea how far you'd go.

08:10.840 --> 08:13.920
What if one day I wake up and realize

08:18.320 --> 08:19.640
you've ruthlessly stolen my innocence?

08:21.080 --> 08:23.520
You really don't have to be so obsessed

08:26.920 --> 08:27.920
with me.

08:29.320 --> 08:31.560
Hold on. Can we just stick to the facts?

08:31.640 --> 08:33.760
I sleepwalked into your room,

08:33.840 --> 08:36.919
accidentally found
a spot on your bed, and fell asleep.

08:37.520 --> 08:38.679
I swear I didn't touch you.

08:38.760 --> 08:40.520
- How do you know?
- I woke up before you.

08:40.600 --> 08:41.880
Oh.

08:43.280 --> 08:44.760
But you, on the other hand,

08:44.840 --> 08:45.960
were all over the place when you slept.

08:47.040 --> 08:48.760
You even pulled me back
when I was about to leave.

08:52.160 --> 08:54.480
I pulled you back? What happened next?

08:56.880 --> 08:58.920
You need to fill me in.

09:00.400 --> 09:02.960
Anyway, you made physical contact with me

09:03.040 --> 09:04.080
while you were still asleep.

09:04.720 --> 09:06.040
I'll just call it even.

09:06.120 --> 09:07.000
Call it even?

09:07.960 --> 09:09.120
Even in terms of what?

09:10.560 --> 09:12.560
The last time when I sleepwalked,
I ended up hugging you.

09:20.920 --> 09:22.320
So, that's how you make things even?

09:23.520 --> 09:25.200
I still got the short end
of the stick then.

09:26.120 --> 09:28.360
It's pretty clear

09:28.440 --> 09:29.960
who's into who here.

09:32.280 --> 09:34.640
I'm really going to be late.
We'll talk about it tonight when I'm back.

09:42.200 --> 09:43.480
Ma.

09:43.560 --> 09:44.600
Ma.

09:45.600 --> 09:47.600
Sir, I'm coming.

09:47.680 --> 09:49.240
Where's my medicine?

09:49.320 --> 09:52.080
Isn't your medicine
always kept in the cabinet?

09:52.160 --> 09:54.360
- There's one packet missing.
- All right. I'll help you look for it.

09:55.400 --> 09:57.040
- Hurry up.
- How is that possible?

10:14.120 --> 10:15.440
How did it end up here?

10:15.520 --> 10:17.640
Sir, I found it.

10:17.720 --> 10:20.880
Why did you throw it away?

10:20.960 --> 10:22.320
What happened to the medicine inside?

10:22.960 --> 10:24.400
It's all gone.

10:24.480 --> 10:25.880
All gone?

10:25.960 --> 10:27.320
Well, if that's the case,

10:27.400 --> 10:29.000
what are you taking today?

10:31.720 --> 10:34.320
I should have gone
for my check-up two days ago,

10:34.400 --> 10:35.920
but I forgot.

10:36.000 --> 10:38.720
Sir, I'm taking you to the hospital now

10:38.800 --> 10:40.160
to see the doctor and get your medicine.

10:40.240 --> 10:41.360
I'll go downstairs to get the car.

10:41.440 --> 10:42.280
Okay.

10:56.320 --> 10:59.200
Sir, just stay here and wait for me.

10:59.280 --> 11:01.000
I'll be back once I park the car.

11:01.080 --> 11:02.160
Don't wander off.

11:02.240 --> 11:03.840
What do you mean?

11:03.920 --> 11:05.640
Where else could I go?

11:05.720 --> 11:07.040
Go park the car now.

11:10.320 --> 11:11.720
Go.

11:24.760 --> 11:27.600
Madam, be careful
to avoid eating those things

11:27.680 --> 11:29.280
the doctor mentioned.

11:29.360 --> 11:31.320
- I will.
- Get plenty of rest.

11:31.400 --> 11:33.440
If you feel unwell again,

11:33.520 --> 11:34.680
feel free to contact me,
and I'll accompany you to the doctor.

11:35.280 --> 11:36.360
Sure.

11:36.440 --> 11:37.840
Madam, please wait here for a moment.

11:37.920 --> 11:39.720
- Let me check it for you.
- Thank you.

11:44.080 --> 11:45.880
- Lin.
- Mr. Ma.

11:45.960 --> 11:47.680
Have you seen Mr. Su?

11:47.760 --> 11:48.880
Mr. Su, the grandpa?

11:48.960 --> 11:50.160
- Yes.
- I haven't seen him.

11:51.800 --> 11:53.720
Oh no, this is not looking good.

11:53.800 --> 11:55.560
- What's wrong?
- I went to park the car

11:55.640 --> 11:56.680
and told him to wait at the door.

11:56.760 --> 11:58.760
When I got there, no one was around.

11:58.840 --> 12:00.000
I even checked upstairs.

12:00.080 --> 12:01.320
Mr. Ma, don't panic.

12:01.400 --> 12:03.960
Hi, can we make an announcement
to look for someone here?

12:04.040 --> 12:05.480
Shall I help you with the announcement?

12:05.560 --> 12:06.680
I'll check it for you.

12:06.760 --> 12:08.080
You can go ask the guard ahead first.

12:08.160 --> 12:09.760
He seemed a bit strange.

12:14.560 --> 12:15.680
And he looked quite anxious.

12:15.760 --> 12:16.720
He was probably trying to find someone.

12:16.800 --> 12:17.840
What happened next?

12:17.920 --> 12:19.120
After that…

12:26.960 --> 12:28.280
He just hailed a taxi and left.

12:28.360 --> 12:30.160
- He hailed a taxi and left?
- Yes.

12:30.240 --> 12:31.800
- Where did he go?
- How should I know?

12:34.640 --> 12:37.320
Do you think Grandpa ran away with her?

12:37.920 --> 12:39.440
No, I didn't say that.

12:39.520 --> 12:40.920
I just said it was possible.

12:41.000 --> 12:42.440
But how could it be such a coincidence?

12:42.520 --> 12:43.640
Fang called in sick this morning,
saying she felt dizzy,

12:43.720 --> 12:45.160
and then Grandpa disappeared.

12:47.280 --> 12:48.440
Honestly, though,

12:48.960 --> 12:50.160
I can't picture what it would be like

12:50.760 --> 12:52.720
to catch someone having an affair.

12:52.800 --> 12:55.240
Could you stop overthinking it?

12:56.560 --> 12:57.600
She answered.

12:58.960 --> 13:01.440
Fang, how are you feeling now?

13:01.520 --> 13:04.320
I got some fruit
and thought I'd come to visit.

13:04.400 --> 13:06.880
Someone's already here to check on me,
so don't worry.

13:08.880 --> 13:11.240
That's even more reason
for me to visit you.

13:11.320 --> 13:12.280
It won't be necessary.

13:12.360 --> 13:14.480
Thank you. Bye.

13:15.280 --> 13:16.120
Did she hang up?

13:22.960 --> 13:24.160
Can we trust the address?

13:24.240 --> 13:25.400
Of course.

13:25.480 --> 13:27.280
I have many friends on Help Me,

13:27.360 --> 13:29.080
so getting an address is easy.

13:31.480 --> 13:33.760
I didn't know you were so resourceful.

13:33.840 --> 13:35.280
This is it.

13:36.520 --> 13:37.360
Is it here?

13:40.040 --> 13:42.040
All right. I got this.

13:46.480 --> 13:47.680
The door is not closed.

13:48.480 --> 13:49.920
- It's not closed.
- Let's go.

13:53.320 --> 13:54.160
Wait.

13:55.200 --> 13:56.720
What if Grandpa is in there?

13:57.240 --> 13:59.040
Aren't we here to find him?

14:03.320 --> 14:04.160
Wait.

14:05.560 --> 14:07.400
- Have you ever done this before?
- Yes.

14:07.480 --> 14:08.680
What should I do then?

14:09.200 --> 14:11.640
- Play it by ear.
- Okay.

14:12.680 --> 14:13.520
Wait.

14:15.920 --> 14:18.560
- What now?
- I need a deep breath.

14:19.600 --> 14:21.400
- Are you ready?
- Yes.

14:22.680 --> 14:23.640
I just don't want to see anyone

14:23.720 --> 14:25.240
- when I'm like this.
- What's the matter?

14:26.680 --> 14:27.760
- What are you doing?
- Quick.

14:27.840 --> 14:29.880
- I'm scared.
- You are already here.

14:29.960 --> 14:31.480
Mr. Su,

14:31.560 --> 14:33.280
I don't want to.

14:33.360 --> 14:35.040
Listen to me. Be good.

14:38.160 --> 14:39.120
An?

14:39.200 --> 14:41.800
Grandpa, you're really here.

14:48.880 --> 14:49.960
Fang is sick,

14:50.040 --> 14:51.920
- so I'm here to check on her.
- What happened just now then?

14:52.000 --> 14:53.160
Just now?

14:54.000 --> 14:56.080
She's being stubborn
and won't take her medicine.

14:56.160 --> 14:58.000
You were supposed to pick up
the medicine at the hospital first.

15:00.080 --> 15:01.880
I saw in the group chat later

15:01.960 --> 15:03.680
that Fang was sick,

15:03.760 --> 15:04.600
so I came to see her. Is that not allowed?

15:04.680 --> 15:06.240
That was on purpose then.

15:07.360 --> 15:08.280
What do you mean?

15:09.240 --> 15:11.040
When did I need you to tell me what to do?

15:11.120 --> 15:13.000
I'll do whatever I want.

15:13.080 --> 15:14.960
Fang, I'm leaving the medicine here.

15:15.040 --> 15:16.920
Be good and take it.

15:17.440 --> 15:18.560
Remember to take it.

15:18.640 --> 15:21.120
- Thank you, and sorry for the trouble.
- I… Wait…

15:21.200 --> 15:24.560
Fang, I hope you get well soon.

15:24.640 --> 15:25.760
I'll leave the fruit here.

15:30.200 --> 15:33.080
Can you take me for a ride on your bike?

15:36.120 --> 15:37.720
Now I understand

15:37.800 --> 15:39.920
why Grandma wanted
to find her own path in life.

15:41.720 --> 15:43.000
When there's no more love
between two people,

15:44.280 --> 15:46.120
there's no point in staying together.

15:46.960 --> 15:47.880
Qiao,

15:49.000 --> 15:50.760
I'm all alone again.

15:51.680 --> 15:55.720
How come you've never talked
about your parents?

15:57.640 --> 15:59.000
They're both gone now.

15:59.080 --> 16:00.960
I have an older brother
who's much better than me.

16:03.480 --> 16:04.520
Since I was little,

16:04.600 --> 16:06.800
I've always been the most
disappointing one in the family.

16:08.840 --> 16:10.360
I'm nothing like my brother.

16:10.440 --> 16:11.800
When compared to him,

16:11.880 --> 16:13.440
I just feel like a burden to everyone.

16:14.720 --> 16:15.960
In 2008, during the Olympics,

16:16.560 --> 16:17.400
I told my dad

16:17.480 --> 16:18.800
I wanted to go to the Bird's Nest
to watch the opening ceremony.

16:18.880 --> 16:20.560
He said he'd take me there

16:20.640 --> 16:22.320
as long as I made it into the top 15

16:22.400 --> 16:23.400
of my class.

16:24.320 --> 16:25.240
But in the end, I ranked 28th.

16:28.280 --> 16:29.960
How many people were there in your class?

16:31.200 --> 16:33.200
- Thirty.
- That's all right.

16:33.280 --> 16:34.160
At least you weren't ranked last.

16:38.760 --> 16:40.200
You'll never understand

16:40.280 --> 16:41.320
what it's like to always be at the bottom

16:41.400 --> 16:43.400
and feeling like I was dragging
everyone down no matter what I did.

16:45.040 --> 16:46.440
I often wonder

16:46.520 --> 16:47.640
if I had done better,

16:48.320 --> 16:50.560
would my whole family
have gone to Beijing together happily?

16:50.640 --> 16:52.880
When my dad saw my grades,

16:52.960 --> 16:53.800
he got really upset.

16:54.760 --> 16:55.880
He was supposed
to take my mom and my brother

16:55.960 --> 16:57.520
to watch the Olympics,

16:57.600 --> 16:59.680
but out of anger, he changed the plans

16:59.760 --> 17:00.680
and headed west instead of north.

17:02.080 --> 17:04.000
Later, due to a rainstorm
and slippery roads,

17:04.079 --> 17:05.440
they got into a car accident
and passed away.

17:09.440 --> 17:11.359
The three most accomplished people
in my family

17:13.400 --> 17:15.280
disappeared from my life all at once.

17:20.079 --> 17:21.400
Do you love them?

17:27.119 --> 17:28.040
Of course, I do.

17:28.600 --> 17:30.000
How could I not love them?

17:30.720 --> 17:33.840
Good then. They must love you too,

17:33.920 --> 17:35.480
but the lack of communication between you

17:36.480 --> 17:38.960
has made it harder to express that love.

17:39.800 --> 17:41.240
My name is Zhong Siqiao.

17:41.320 --> 17:43.320
Perhaps because of the "Qiao" in my name,

17:43.400 --> 17:45.640
I often find myself beneath bridges,

17:46.520 --> 17:48.280
gazing at one after another,

17:48.360 --> 17:50.640
wondering how many people

17:50.720 --> 17:52.760
they've helped to connect.

17:54.440 --> 17:56.120
And suddenly, I feel a sense of hope.

17:57.120 --> 17:59.840
With a bridge, you can reach another city

18:00.680 --> 18:02.480
or the beginning of a new dream.

18:03.480 --> 18:05.520
Isn't that how relationships work too?

18:07.120 --> 18:10.160
You have a bridge hidden in your heart.

18:10.240 --> 18:11.960
Once you cross it,

18:13.200 --> 18:14.800
you'll realize that many people love you.

18:15.440 --> 18:17.240
- Really?
- Absolutely.

18:17.320 --> 18:19.480
Real love isn't earned
by buying others handbags

18:19.560 --> 18:21.880
or getting first place in class.

18:22.800 --> 18:25.680
It's something you receive
by offering your genuine love.

19:00.440 --> 19:01.720
It smells amazing.

19:06.800 --> 19:07.680
Yum.

19:17.040 --> 19:19.520
Someone rarely asks me to eat out,

19:20.240 --> 19:21.520
and yet she seems so lost in thought.

19:28.560 --> 19:29.880
I sleepwalked again.

19:31.280 --> 19:32.960
Did the sleeping bag I gave you not work?

19:33.040 --> 19:35.320
I accidentally forgot
to use it last night.

19:37.720 --> 19:39.120
So, what did you do this time?

19:43.360 --> 19:44.200
Qiao,

19:45.080 --> 19:47.000
- can I ask you something?
- Ask away.

19:47.800 --> 19:48.640
Didn't you end up

19:49.960 --> 19:53.880
in the same bed with Su Haoan by accident?

19:54.400 --> 19:57.560
Did he apologize to you afterward

19:57.640 --> 20:01.960
or offer any compensation?

20:05.120 --> 20:09.400
Technically,
I was the one who got into his bed,

20:10.560 --> 20:12.120
so it's me who owes him.

20:15.840 --> 20:17.800
So, how do you intend
to make it up to him?

20:17.880 --> 20:20.160
It's not like a debt
that needs to be repaid.

20:20.240 --> 20:21.720
How am I supposed
to make it right with him?

20:23.680 --> 20:24.600
So, that's how you make things even?

20:25.440 --> 20:26.960
I still got the short end
of the stick then.

20:28.000 --> 20:31.920
It's pretty clear who's into who here.

20:33.800 --> 20:36.360
But he seems to feel like
he's been taken advantage of.

20:37.400 --> 20:38.960
What? Who?

20:40.720 --> 20:42.720
No one, just a friend of mine.

20:47.760 --> 20:50.200
So, did Su Haonan ask you

20:50.280 --> 20:52.520
for an apology or any
kind of compensation afterward?

20:52.600 --> 20:53.640
I'm a girl.

20:53.720 --> 20:56.480
If he's making a big deal out of this,
that's kind of petty.

20:58.000 --> 20:59.720
But during the Spring Festival,
I pretended to be his girlfriend

20:59.800 --> 21:01.080
and had dinner with his grandparents.

21:01.160 --> 21:02.080
I guess that makes up for it, right?

21:02.160 --> 21:03.360
You even pretended to be his girlfriend?

21:03.440 --> 21:06.160
It was only for show.
I was merely doing him a favor.

21:06.240 --> 21:08.120
I won't get involved in his matters again.

21:10.600 --> 21:12.360
How long do I have to keep
making up for this?

21:14.000 --> 21:15.960
See, here we go again.

21:17.800 --> 21:18.800
Hello.

21:19.560 --> 21:21.240
Oh, it's you, Mr. Ma. What's the matter?

21:21.320 --> 21:24.920
Mr. Su kept talking about a car accident

21:25.000 --> 21:26.040
and someone being in urgent care,

21:26.120 --> 21:29.640
but he couldn't give a clear location.

21:29.720 --> 21:32.320
I tried calling Haoan,
but there was no answer.

21:32.400 --> 21:33.760
Okay, I'm on my way there now.

21:34.360 --> 21:36.720
- What's wrong?
- It seems like something's happened.

21:36.800 --> 21:38.600
I'll let you know once I figure it out.

21:38.680 --> 21:40.640
- Ride safe.
- Okay.

21:41.440 --> 21:43.120
I'm off. Stay safe.

21:54.120 --> 21:56.920
Mr. Su, do you know
where Haoan had the accident?

21:57.000 --> 21:58.400
Let's go pick up Grandma first.

21:59.720 --> 22:00.640
Grandma?

22:01.360 --> 22:03.520
Grandma, where are you going?

22:03.600 --> 22:05.880
You're not planning to drive off
and travel again, are you?

22:05.960 --> 22:07.040
If I don't go traveling,

22:07.120 --> 22:08.440
am I supposed to just stay here
looking after this old man?

22:09.600 --> 22:11.600
I thought you had already left.

22:12.200 --> 22:15.120
I was going to leave
as soon as we finished talking.

22:15.720 --> 22:17.000
Grandma isn't in Nanwu.

22:17.840 --> 22:20.040
Grandpa, do you know
which hospital Haoan is at?

22:23.040 --> 22:24.960
Hey, Grandpa said
you were in a car accident.

22:25.040 --> 22:26.000
Are you injured?

22:26.600 --> 22:27.960
What? I'm at work.

22:28.040 --> 22:29.120
I've just finished a meeting.

22:29.720 --> 22:30.560
Grandpa,

22:30.640 --> 22:32.720
Haoan says he's at work
and has just finished a meeting.

22:32.800 --> 22:35.760
It's not An, but his parents.

22:35.840 --> 22:36.800
They got into a car accident

22:36.880 --> 22:38.080
and are now at the hospital.

22:38.160 --> 22:40.800
Grandpa, how about you talk to Haoan?

22:41.640 --> 22:43.560
Hello, Grandma.

22:44.440 --> 22:45.520
Who is this?

22:46.120 --> 22:47.560
Well… Who's this?

22:47.640 --> 22:49.120
Hurry up.

22:49.200 --> 22:50.600
What is Grandpa babbling about?

22:51.160 --> 22:52.680
Wait. Grandpa's confused,
and you're just following suit.

22:52.760 --> 22:53.600
What's going on?

22:54.400 --> 22:56.120
Maybe I should talk to you later.

22:56.200 --> 22:57.440
All right.

23:09.200 --> 23:12.320
Sorry for making you worry.

23:17.520 --> 23:19.800
When I was out with Wood,

23:22.080 --> 23:24.120
I saw a car flip over.

23:24.200 --> 23:26.280
Good dog, Wood.

23:35.280 --> 23:36.280
There were many people

23:37.360 --> 23:38.640
trapped under the car.

23:38.720 --> 23:40.160
AMBULANCE

23:41.200 --> 23:42.320
I suddenly remembered

23:43.000 --> 23:44.000
the car crash

23:45.040 --> 23:47.520
involving An's parents,

23:48.440 --> 23:51.680
but I was so confused

23:52.800 --> 23:54.480
that I thought it was actually happening.

23:55.040 --> 23:56.960
It hurts so much.

23:59.000 --> 24:01.240
I need to help them.

24:01.320 --> 24:02.640
It's all my fault.

24:06.400 --> 24:08.680
The one who suffers the most is An.

24:09.840 --> 24:10.680
He's lost his parents

24:10.760 --> 24:12.920
at such a young age.

24:15.320 --> 24:16.360
An,

24:17.240 --> 24:18.800
don't be afraid.

24:18.880 --> 24:21.240
Grandpa and Grandma will take care of you.

24:21.320 --> 24:22.720
- Be good.
- Grandpa.

24:28.080 --> 24:29.600
Grandpa, what are you doing?

24:31.240 --> 24:32.680
I'm all grown up now.

25:03.120 --> 25:04.440
No need to worry about me. I'm fine.

25:04.520 --> 25:06.560
Who's worried about you?
I'm worried about this one here.

25:06.640 --> 25:08.520
Why is it so sleepy
in the middle of the day?

25:09.080 --> 25:10.480
It's getting old.

25:11.240 --> 25:12.840
Lately, it's always
been sleeping when I see it.

25:14.800 --> 25:15.840
How old is it?

25:16.640 --> 25:17.560
I'm not sure,

25:18.280 --> 25:19.120
but it's pretty old.

25:22.520 --> 25:23.400
Grandpa's the same.

25:25.760 --> 25:26.760
When people grow old,

25:26.840 --> 25:28.960
it's inevitable they'll have moments
where they just don't make sense.

25:29.600 --> 25:31.560
They will often behave like a child.

25:32.280 --> 25:34.040
My dad isn't that old yet,

25:34.120 --> 25:35.840
but he's also very stubborn now,

25:35.920 --> 25:36.800
and it's hard to reason with him.

25:39.800 --> 25:42.000
Wood, she's badmouthing you. Bite her.

25:42.080 --> 25:43.800
Are you implying something about Grandpa?

25:50.320 --> 25:53.080
2008 was also the year my parents

25:53.160 --> 25:54.320
passed away in a car accident.

25:55.800 --> 25:58.280
On the day my parents
and my brother were being laid to rest,

25:58.360 --> 25:59.920
Grandpa wouldn't let me go
to the burial site.

26:00.840 --> 26:03.000
That was the hardest moment of my life.

26:10.160 --> 26:11.720
When I came back from the funeral,

26:13.840 --> 26:15.320
I found it curled up alone by the door,

26:16.000 --> 26:18.000
motionless, like a block of wood.

26:18.840 --> 26:20.720
Wherever I went, it followed,

26:21.480 --> 26:22.720
and I couldn't chase it away.

26:24.400 --> 26:25.800
At that moment,

26:30.920 --> 26:33.320
I actually felt quite
sympathetic toward it.

26:34.600 --> 26:35.920
Just like me, it lost its parents

26:37.320 --> 26:38.680
and its support.

26:39.640 --> 26:41.520
So, I decided to adopt it.

26:42.320 --> 26:44.200
Why didn't you let it stay with you then?

26:44.840 --> 26:45.880
Every time I see it,

26:46.440 --> 26:48.240
I'm reminded of how I felt back then.

27:14.400 --> 27:15.840
Why are you back so late?

27:21.440 --> 27:23.120
I have a lot of orders today.

27:26.240 --> 27:29.520
We can grab some supper together later.

27:30.160 --> 27:31.400
I'm not hungry.

27:31.480 --> 27:32.920
But I am.

27:39.760 --> 27:42.080
The one who suffers the most is An.

27:42.160 --> 27:43.440
Don't be afraid.

27:44.280 --> 27:46.200
Grandpa and Grandma will take care of you.

27:53.440 --> 27:55.600
Qiao. Sweetheart,

27:56.600 --> 27:57.960
you're all grown up.

27:58.040 --> 27:59.040
Why are you still acting like this?

27:59.120 --> 28:01.240
Is there a certain age
when you're not allowed to act like that?

28:02.040 --> 28:02.880
No.

28:03.760 --> 28:05.040
It's just you haven't hugged me in ages.

28:05.120 --> 28:06.560
What, I can't hug you?

28:07.320 --> 28:08.720
Of course, you can.

28:10.480 --> 28:11.560
Hold on.

28:13.320 --> 28:16.400
Were you bullied out there?

28:16.920 --> 28:18.240
Did someone bully you?

28:18.320 --> 28:20.080
- Tell me.
- No.

28:21.440 --> 28:23.480
- Really?
- I just wanted to hug you.

28:23.560 --> 28:25.160
Why are you making such a fuss?

28:25.240 --> 28:26.680
Now, I feel relieved.

28:28.320 --> 28:29.880
You go home first

28:30.440 --> 28:32.440
and have your mom
cook me a bowl of noodles.

28:33.200 --> 28:34.800
I'll head back in a bit.

28:35.480 --> 28:37.880
Okay. Come back soon.

28:47.680 --> 28:50.040
- I'll leave now.
- Stay safe.

28:58.160 --> 28:59.080
You are back.

28:59.160 --> 29:01.400
My dad says he's hungry
and wants some noodles.

29:02.720 --> 29:04.320
I was just about to go to bed.

29:04.400 --> 29:06.000
You cook the noodles for your dad.

29:13.120 --> 29:14.120
What happened?

29:15.160 --> 29:17.400
You look so pale. Are you sick?

29:18.040 --> 29:20.240
It's nothing.
I think I just caught a cold.

29:22.240 --> 29:23.520
You think this is nothing?

29:23.600 --> 29:25.200
Rest for a few days.

29:25.280 --> 29:27.760
You're a girl, yet you spend all day

29:27.840 --> 29:29.600
buried in work,

29:29.680 --> 29:31.240
never taking care of yourself.

29:31.760 --> 29:33.360
How will you ever find a partner?

29:33.440 --> 29:35.040
Mom, stop nagging me.

29:35.760 --> 29:36.680
All right.

29:40.000 --> 29:42.040
I'll make some noodles for your dad later.

29:42.120 --> 29:43.360
Take this medicine

29:43.440 --> 29:45.240
and get some sleep.

29:46.240 --> 29:47.160
Okay.

29:47.240 --> 29:48.520
Don't stay up late.

29:52.840 --> 29:54.800
Qiao, you mustn't get sick.

29:54.880 --> 29:56.400
I'm stuck on some homework,

29:56.480 --> 29:57.600
and Mom won't let me sleep.

29:57.680 --> 29:59.400
You've got to help me.

29:59.480 --> 30:01.640
Guoqiang, leave your sister alone.

30:01.720 --> 30:03.680
Can't you see she's not feeling well?

30:03.760 --> 30:04.600
Do your homework by yourself.

30:08.240 --> 30:09.480
Mom, it's fine.

30:11.320 --> 30:12.440
Which questions are you stuck on?

30:12.520 --> 30:13.560
Let me take a look.

30:17.760 --> 30:21.160
NANWU TV STATION

30:22.360 --> 30:24.360
If you come any later, it'll be all gone.
Hurry up.

30:29.920 --> 30:30.760
SANG YAN

30:31.400 --> 30:32.520
When will you be back?

30:41.560 --> 30:42.520
Wen Yifan.

30:44.600 --> 30:46.000
Why are you here?

30:47.400 --> 30:48.440
Explain yourself.

30:50.200 --> 30:51.240
Honestly,

30:53.280 --> 30:54.440
I'm a little scared.

30:55.520 --> 30:57.320
I have no idea how far you'd go.

30:57.400 --> 31:00.640
What if one day I wake up and realize

31:04.880 --> 31:06.560
you've ruthlessly stolen my innocence?

31:12.120 --> 31:13.760
I've got something to handle today,

31:13.840 --> 31:15.600
so I won't be home early.

31:15.680 --> 31:17.920
We'll talk another time.

31:30.480 --> 31:31.520
Mu Chengyun.

31:33.960 --> 31:36.080
- What is it, Yifan?
- Didn't you want me

31:36.160 --> 31:37.480
to help you pick a gift?

31:37.560 --> 31:39.480
- Do you still need my help?
- What?

31:42.560 --> 31:43.400
We got off work early today.

31:43.480 --> 31:44.720
Sure.

31:45.400 --> 31:46.680
Thanks, Yifan.

31:54.560 --> 31:55.720
Wen Yifan,

31:57.600 --> 32:00.320
one must take responsibility
for their actions.

32:06.000 --> 32:07.440
Okay. Got it.

32:07.520 --> 32:09.480
I'll try to be back as early as possible.

32:10.600 --> 32:11.760
Does he really
have to interfere this much?

32:12.400 --> 32:14.440
You two are nothing
more than roommates, right?

32:15.360 --> 32:17.040
We have an agreement for co-renting.

32:18.600 --> 32:19.480
Speaking of which,

32:19.560 --> 32:21.160
the senior we're buying a gift for

32:21.240 --> 32:23.440
was actually
in the same class as Sang Yan.

32:23.520 --> 32:25.360
He got married right after graduation,

32:25.440 --> 32:26.800
and now he even has a child.

32:27.880 --> 32:29.080
Yifan,

32:29.160 --> 32:30.920
how did you and Sang Yan meet?

32:31.440 --> 32:32.840
I remember you graduated

32:32.920 --> 32:34.160
from Yihe University, right?

32:35.000 --> 32:36.160
We were high school classmates.

32:36.240 --> 32:37.840
High school classmates?

32:38.360 --> 32:39.640
Not first love or anything?

32:41.000 --> 32:41.960
No.

32:42.640 --> 32:45.600
I heard that Sang Yan

32:45.680 --> 32:47.800
had a girl he really liked in high school,

32:48.360 --> 32:49.600
but he never managed to win her heart.

32:49.680 --> 32:52.040
Even after graduating from university,
he still couldn't forget her.

32:53.240 --> 32:54.320
I'm not sure.

32:55.520 --> 32:56.920
I'm really curious.

32:57.000 --> 32:58.200
What kind of person

32:58.280 --> 33:00.400
could make someone
as outstanding as Sang Yan

33:00.480 --> 33:01.800
like her for so long?

33:03.120 --> 33:06.240
At the graduation gathering,
someone even asked

33:06.840 --> 33:09.040
if he was heartbroken
because the unattainable

33:09.120 --> 33:10.560
always seems the best.

33:10.640 --> 33:12.600
You remember what he said

33:13.120 --> 33:14.880
- at the gathering?
- Yeah,

33:15.520 --> 33:18.200
I remember now. He said,

33:20.280 --> 33:22.280
"Do you really think
I'm that sentimental?"

33:23.960 --> 33:25.800
Why would he say that?

33:25.880 --> 33:26.840
Why wouldn't he?

33:28.200 --> 33:29.560
He's too proud

33:30.240 --> 33:32.680
to reveal his vulnerabilities
in front of others.

33:33.400 --> 33:34.840
You seem to know him pretty well.

33:38.440 --> 33:41.120
Maybe he was just joking
after drinking too much.

33:42.880 --> 33:44.560
Couldn't it be that he drank too much

33:44.640 --> 33:47.280
and used a joke
to say what he really felt?

33:55.160 --> 33:56.800
Yifan, thanks for today.

33:57.320 --> 33:58.440
How about strolling around a bit more?

33:58.520 --> 34:01.040
Or is there something
you'd like to eat? My treat.

34:01.120 --> 34:02.480
No, thanks.

34:09.880 --> 34:13.120
I recall that Sang Yan
also said something else.

34:13.920 --> 34:16.840
He mentioned
that if he ever met that person again,

34:16.920 --> 34:18.360
he'd still be good to her,

34:18.440 --> 34:20.800
but his attitude would be different.

34:21.480 --> 34:23.400
So, whoever he's being nice to now

34:23.480 --> 34:24.840
should watch out.

34:24.920 --> 34:27.760
Maybe he has an ulterior motive,
like with you.

34:28.639 --> 34:30.040
- Me?
- Yes.

34:30.760 --> 34:32.159
Haven't you watched revenge dramas?

34:32.239 --> 34:33.239
It's always the same plot.

34:33.800 --> 34:36.480
They'll act like they care,
treat you nicely,

34:36.560 --> 34:37.719
and when you're deeply invested

34:37.800 --> 34:38.920
and can't withdraw,

34:39.000 --> 34:40.760
they ruthlessly abandon you

34:40.840 --> 34:42.120
to complete their revenge.

34:43.159 --> 34:46.440
Didn't you say he only said
one sentence that night?

34:48.480 --> 34:49.560
Did I say that?

34:50.480 --> 34:51.360
I don't really remember.

34:51.440 --> 34:53.600
Maybe I was drunk and got it wrong.

34:54.400 --> 34:55.520
In our line of work,

34:55.600 --> 34:58.520
it's fine to joke around
and gossip outside work.

34:58.600 --> 34:59.640
But when it comes to journalism,

34:59.720 --> 35:00.840
we can't have this kind of attitude.

35:00.920 --> 35:02.720
Thanks for telling me this,

35:02.800 --> 35:04.520
but when it comes to relationships,

35:04.600 --> 35:06.200
I might not be less experienced than you.

35:09.480 --> 35:11.880
I may not know much about relationships.

35:12.640 --> 35:14.200
But I believe

35:14.280 --> 35:17.480
what matters is sincerity, not experience.

35:23.360 --> 35:26.640
Just like a first love, pure and sweet,

35:28.280 --> 35:30.960
with a heart that only wants
to bring joy to the other person,

35:31.040 --> 35:32.840
without expecting anything in return.

35:35.520 --> 35:37.240
Anyway, you got what you needed,
so I'll head home now.

35:40.040 --> 35:41.160
Bye, Yifan.

36:18.440 --> 36:20.960
Well. You are…

36:21.040 --> 36:21.920
You still remember to come back?

36:22.000 --> 36:23.200
Didn't we agree

36:23.280 --> 36:25.680
to dress appropriately in shared spaces?

36:39.440 --> 36:41.040
I've already accepted my fate.

36:44.760 --> 36:45.760
What do you mean?

36:47.360 --> 36:49.480
You've already kissed me and touched me.

36:49.560 --> 36:52.280
Does it even matter
whether I'm wearing clothes now?

36:55.920 --> 36:57.480
Have you been drinking?

37:00.800 --> 37:02.960
Then I'll keep it short.

37:03.040 --> 37:04.400
After what happened this morning,

37:04.480 --> 37:05.440
I realized I might
have no sense of direction

37:05.520 --> 37:06.960
when I'm sleepwalking.

37:07.040 --> 37:08.960
Blocking the door with a chair won't help.

37:09.040 --> 37:10.800
From now on, you'll need
to lock your door at night.

37:10.880 --> 37:12.400
I'll also go to the hospital soon…

37:14.200 --> 37:15.040
Are you…

37:16.560 --> 37:17.760
blushing?

37:21.040 --> 37:22.840
And follow the doctor's advice.

37:32.680 --> 37:33.720
Why are you blushing?

37:38.560 --> 37:39.960
It's too hot!

37:40.520 --> 37:42.480
Haven't you noticed
how hot it's been lately?

37:47.240 --> 37:51.200
I… I just haven't seen
a guy's body like that before.

37:51.280 --> 37:54.960
Besides, before we moved in together,
we made an agreement.

37:55.040 --> 37:57.360
I said you couldn't wear

37:57.440 --> 37:59.240
revealing clothes in shared spaces,
and you agreed.

37:59.320 --> 38:00.640
You even said I must be dreaming.

38:01.360 --> 38:02.840
I did say that,

38:02.920 --> 38:04.240
but I'm in a good mood today,

38:04.320 --> 38:05.720
so I'll indulge you a little.

38:08.240 --> 38:09.800
I'll try to make sure

38:09.880 --> 38:11.080
this doesn't happen again.

38:11.160 --> 38:12.200
You should be more careful as well, okay?

38:12.280 --> 38:14.400
You handle things the same way every time.

38:15.160 --> 38:16.760
But what's the result?

38:16.840 --> 38:18.240
In the end,

38:18.320 --> 38:19.640
you still end up doing it again.

38:21.600 --> 38:23.880
Tell me what you want then,
and I'll do my best to cooperate.

38:30.600 --> 38:32.600
I have just one request.

38:39.000 --> 38:40.600
Until you find

38:42.240 --> 38:44.400
a real solution to this,

38:45.960 --> 38:47.360
could you

38:48.160 --> 38:51.400
keep your distance from other men?

38:54.280 --> 38:55.200
Let them stay away.

38:56.280 --> 38:58.960
Don't spend time with them while making me

39:01.320 --> 39:04.200
your little pushover
who lets you get handsy

39:05.520 --> 39:09.120
whenever you feel like it.

39:14.800 --> 39:17.280
Shall I take pity

39:18.280 --> 39:19.600
on you then?

39:21.280 --> 39:22.600
Thanks for your coopration.

39:34.280 --> 39:35.480
Take pity on me?

39:41.360 --> 39:42.200
Yifan, wait.

39:43.560 --> 39:45.960
I was so uncomfortable
when Mu Chengyun touched me,

39:47.280 --> 39:49.400
yet I didn't mind Sang Yan touching me.

39:51.040 --> 39:54.880
Could you keep
your distance from other men?

39:56.120 --> 39:57.520
Why did he say that?

39:58.480 --> 39:59.920
It's as if I'm his girl…

40:17.120 --> 40:19.400
I do seem to treat him differently.

40:22.280 --> 40:25.440
Yes, only him.

40:26.440 --> 40:27.800
But why?

40:33.160 --> 40:34.640
Do I still have feelings for him?

40:53.400 --> 40:59.280
THE STORY IS NOT OVER YET…

40:59.360 --> 41:01.000
I can't sleepwalk again tonight,

41:01.680 --> 41:03.160
or he'll have trouble sleeping.

41:11.320 --> 41:12.160
These are…

41:14.480 --> 41:16.240
Why are there suddenly more lights?

41:26.440 --> 41:27.920
And all these safety measures…

41:41.800 --> 41:42.840
Were they

41:43.400 --> 41:45.120
all set up for me?

41:52.560 --> 41:54.120
Why are you sleeping here?

41:55.800 --> 41:57.720
Sorry for startling you.

41:58.760 --> 42:00.280
I might have been sleepwalking.

42:04.320 --> 42:05.520
What’s that supposed to mean?

42:07.120 --> 42:08.080
Are you mocking me,

42:10.480 --> 42:11.840
or is this revenge?

42:14.880 --> 42:17.440
Well, that will make us even then.

42:21.880 --> 42:23.280
Get some sleep and lock the door.

42:40.760 --> 42:42.440
Did I misunderstand him?

45:27.800 --> 45:28.920
HUGE THANKS TO EVERYONE INVOLVED
AND TO ALL THE FANS OF THE FIRST FROST!

45:29.000 --> 45:30.080
TREAT YOURSELF WELL
AND THE WORLD WILL HOLD MORE LOVE FOR YOU!
